Yes — this looks worth reaching out on. @@entity:disco-pharmaceuticals|DISCO Pharmaceuticals|type:company@@ fits a JPM-style outbound screen because it is fresh, financable, and specific: Cologne, Germany; €36M Seed announced 2025-12-11; surfaceome mapping platform; lead ADC candidates; CEO Mark Manfredi; founder Roman Thomas {{fact:ground_truth:DISCO}}. For banker purposes, the freshness window is good (16 days old / within banker window), so this is not a stale name {{fact:ground_truth:DISCO}}.

What I’d do with it: treat DISCO as an **active outreach candidate**, but not a blind generic email. Lead with a tight hypothesis around next financing/strategic needs: platform/company-building after a large seed, partnerability around ADC and bispecific programs, and likely future capital/BD planning tied to SCLC and MSS-CRC program development {{fact:ground_truth:DISCO}}. Best next steps: 1) add to this week’s priority pipeline, 2) draft a 5-sentence outreach to CEO Mark Manfredi or the primary contact info@discopharma.de, 3) verify the primary source announcement and investor context before sending, and 4) prepare two angles—capital formation and strategic partnering—rather than a broad “intro” {{fact:ground_truth:DISCO}}.

